-- Peru Lending to Expand 15% in 2012, La Republica Says
-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 2012-02-03T15:35:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-03/peru-lending-to-expand-15-in-2012-la-republica-says.html
Peru’s outstanding bank loan growth
will ease to 15 percent this year from a 17 percent pace last
year as the economy slows, La Republica  reported .  Lenders’ non-performing loan ratio will be about 1.5
percent, the Lima-based newspaper said, citing comments by
Alberto Morisaki, head of research at the country’s banking
association known as  Asbanc .  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
